Maybe they just went to the restroom.

201
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:49,400
What? Both of them at the same time?

202
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:52,320
Well...maybe they just had to
pee at the same time.

203
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,720
I don't think that's it.

204
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,040
Listen to me.

205
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,120
I've filmed every single inch of this plane.

206
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,120
There's not a single soul in there.

207
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:03,080
Don't you think that's weird?

208
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:06,880
Dear passengers,
this is Captain Ekasit Ayasan speaking.

209
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,440
See? The Captain is making an announcement.

210
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:13,440
We are currently cruising
at an altitude of approximately 35,000 feet.

211
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:16,440
The seatbelt sign will remain on...

212
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,440
until weather conditions permit.

213
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,160
Something's not right.

214
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,520
So...

215
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:24,440
in

216
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,400
short...

217
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,600
what

218
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,320
is it?

219
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,320
Wait!

220
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,360
There are no pilots...

221
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,840
on this aircraft!

222
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,320
Everyone!

223
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,160
Everyone!

224
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,880
Everyone!

225
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,880
Hey, Chaba,
would you stop shouting "everyone" for once?

226
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:56,640
What's the matter?
You think you're at a town hall meeting?

227
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:58,520
Why do you keep calling out to everyone?

228
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,480
And you know what, this "everyone" stuff...

229
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,720
it's just your stuff...

230
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,080
Right.

231
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,200
Wait, hold on, Chai,
are you stealing my lines now?

232
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,920
Anyway, what is it, Chaba?

233
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:12,920
I'm trying to tell you that
this plane has no pilots!

234
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,800
See? It's just about...

235
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,240
Everyone!

236
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,880
What is all this noise?

237
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,560
The pilots are gone!

238
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,960
We are flying without any pilots!

239
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,760
And did you see this with your own eyes?

240
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:31,760
Yes! Sky and I saw it with our own eyes!

241
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,440
Ladies and gentlemen,
please don't be afraid.

242
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,520
First, take out your phones
and start filming!

243
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,760
Wait...

244
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:44,240
just Penelope, you film this.

245
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:44,880
Got it?

246
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:45,880
I'm filming.

247
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:46,880
Perfect.

248
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,600
In that case, I am deducting one point
from both Chaba and Sky.

249
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,840
Huh?

250
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,760
What?

251
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,000
