without permission...

252
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,800
and for causing such a panic
among the passengers.

253
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,880
But the plane has no pilots!

254
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:01,920
Yes, and I'm docking another point
for being too loud.

255
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:04,000
Stop docking points!
Are you out of your mind?

256
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,240
Another point for talking back
to your supervisor.

257
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,080
Fine, dock them!

258
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:11,040
Today is my last day anyway!

259
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,600
Then I'll dock one point from Sky.

260
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,040
Hey! What did I do?

261
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,400
For failing to warn your friend.

262
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,320
Chaba!

263
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:18,360
This isn't fair, Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

264
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,160
Are you going to protest?

265
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,880
If you protest, I'll dock another one.

266
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,640
Ms. Petchgam Ploy, maybe you should
stop docking points for a second.

267
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:26,640
The fact that our plane has no pilots
is a much bigger deal, don't you think?

268
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:29,720
Actually, it's not a big deal at all, Chai.

269
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:32,320
Because our aircraft
is operated by an AI system.

270
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,120
It's the latest technology.

271
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:35,360
Therefore, we take off with AI...

272
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,760
and we will land softly with AI as well.

273
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,720
Don't worry, everything is very smooth.

274
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:42,720
Well, why didn't you tell us that
in the first place?

275
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,360
Look! The plane's exploding!

276
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,960
Shut up!

277
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,800
AI can handle something like this,
right, Ms. Petchgam Ploy?

278
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,240
It cannot.

279
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,240
The program does not have a system
to prevent the plane from exploding.

280
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:08,800
Wait, one of us needs to go
and save this plane right now!

281
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,480
Why did it have to be us?

282
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:18,480
Exactly.
What criteria did she even use to choose?

283
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:22,880
Well, at least it's not just the two of us.

284
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:27,760
But that other one she brought along...
I can't tell if he's an asset or a burden.

285
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,880
He's definitely a burden.
Ms. Petchgam Ploy....

286
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:33,080
of all people to choose,
she chose Kreetha.

287
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:36,400
Ms. Petchgam Ploy chose me...

288
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,720
What is wrong with you?

289
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,520
Why are you being shy?

290
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:41,040
She chose you for work!

291
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:42,360
I think I know now...

292
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:44,400
why she chose Kreetha.

293
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:47,400
Because he's the only one
who can solve this problem.

294
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,040
She sent him here to...

295
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:49,320
to...

296
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:49,920
to...

297
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:50,840
to...

298
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:51,640
to...

299
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:52,360
to...

300
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,800
To go get All-New
to fly the plane instead of him!

301
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,080
It's a good thing it's not just us.

302
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,560
Go get All-New to fly the plane!

303
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,200
Yeah, let him go get him!

304
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,600
Uh, I don't think so.

305
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,160
All-New...

306
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:06,520
He...

307
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:07,840
He...

308
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,280
He...

309
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:15,240
Why did it never occur to me...

310
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:18,920
that I might be descended from ancestors
in the heart of the Amazon?

311
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,160
Or the Taiga?

312
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:22,760
Or even Huai Kha Khaeng?

313
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:25,960
Anyway, this version of All-New...

314
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,960
is ready to return to his ancestral spirit.

315
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,160
Alright.

316
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,640
Nothing's happening.

317
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:53,120
Does this mean it's not working?

318
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,400
How should I know?

319
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,080
There's no sound effect or anything.

320
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,080
Well...

321
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,760
Damn, there are so many buttons.

322
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,680
Then...

323
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,680
Try this one.

324
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,520
This has to be it.

325
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,200
It's glowing.

326
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,160
That's not it.

327
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,480
The button you just pressed is for Karaoke.

328
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,920
It says so right here.

329
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,200
Hey, I bet...

330
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,640
It's gotta be a pink one like this.

331
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:22,800
I think this is it!

332
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,280
Whoa!

333
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,560
There's a movie to watch too?
This is amazing!

334
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,680
Whoa...

335
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:29,720
So fancy.

336
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:32,600
Is this a cockpit or a karaoke room?

337
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:35,000
Guys, seriously...

338
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
step aside, let me do it.

339
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,600
Press the right one!

340
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:49,640
The red light is on.
I think we're screwed. This isn't it.

341
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:50,360
Whoa!

342
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,360
Hey!

343
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:58,160
Oh, there's instant noodles too!

344
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,320
I'm actually starving right now.

345
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:02,040
Here, you take this one.
I'll press for another.

346
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,240
Stop!

347
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:07,040
Nothing we're doing is
helping with the flying at all.

348
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,720
I think I know what to do.

349
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,800
I'm going to find a way to help you guys.

350
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,280
Just wait for me here.

351
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,280
Got it?

352
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,400
Okay.

353
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,040
Where are you going?

354
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,520
Holy shit!

355
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:24,000
The plane has no pilots!
What are we going to do, Kreetha?

356
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,840
We're all going to freaking die here!

357
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:31,960
Tell you what...
'll give myself to you.

358
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:32,800
Huh?

359
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,840
I'm ready.

360
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,760
Sky, what are you doing?

361
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,000
Please, be my husband!

362
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,360
Chaba, you look gorgeous!

363
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,000
Chaba!

364
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,800
Huh?

365
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:50,440
Is this your way of solving the problem?

366
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,840
Yeah, so what?

367
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:54,040
Penelope, can you actually fly a plane?

368
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,360
I can.

369
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,240
Wait, do you believe me?

370
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:57,840
You're so stupid.

371
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,240
Then why did you bring her in here?

372
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:01,640
Well, to help me film my videos,
obviously!

373
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:02,600
Chaba!

374
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,160
The plane is literally about to crash!

375
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,800
And you're still looking for content?

376
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,920
Think about it, how many influencers...

377
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,800
get the chance to be in the pilot's seat...

378
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,440
get an amazing footage...

379
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,600
She has to help me film.

380
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,000
Guys, listen!

381
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,120
Chaba, I think we really need to hurry.

382
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:18,520
The backup engine display says
we only have ten minutes left!

383
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:21,080
Wait, Kreetha...

384
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,360
do you actually know about planes?

385
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:23,360
Do you?

386
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,400
It's not that hard.

387
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:28,280
Look, it's written right there
on the screen.

388
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:29,120
He's right.

389
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,000
I know now!

390
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,040
Stop "knowing" things!

391
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,520
Because you never
actually know anything!

392
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,120
I don't know how to fly a plane...

393
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:36,800
but I know who can.

394
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,240
My assistant can fly it.

395
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:42,080
Penelope literally just said she can't!

396
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,320
I can!

397
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,600
I can fly a spaceship!

398
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:47,400
I'm not talking about Penelope.

399
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:49,400
I'm talking about my butler.

400
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,920
You have a butler too?

401
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:51,920
Yes.

402
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,840
It's just that he's not on this flight.

403
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,760
Then why even mention it?

404
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,280
Just because he's not here
doesn't mean I can't call him.

405
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:59,240
One phone call and it's done.

406
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,600
Oh.

407
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,760
Wait, don't, Chaba!

408
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,200
The phone signal...

409
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:08,000
it can interfere with the AI flight system!
Don't!

410
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,320
How do you know that?

411
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:11,200
Look right there!

412
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,320
Phone signals...

413
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:16,400
can interfere with the AI flight system.

414
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:21,040
Oh no, the power's out!
What do we do?

415
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,840
There's nothing we can do now, Sky.

416
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:26,000
The plane is going down!

417
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:29,680
Don't just jump to conclusions.
Calm down, calm down.

418
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:32,400
Chaba, I'm not jumping to conclusions!

419
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,680
I read that!

420
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:37,640
The plane is crashing!

421
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,560
Keep it down.

422
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,200
Calm down, stay calm.

423
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,680
Once you jump,

424
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:55,400
count to ten in your head
before pulling the strap.

425
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:57,240
The parachute will deploy automatically.

426
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:59,240
Don't worry, everyone.
Everything will be okay.

427
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:04,600
Calm down, please.
Stay calm, everyone.

428
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,040
Is everyone ready?

429
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:09,440
Okay, everyone's set.

430
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:09,840
Get ready!

431
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,440
One, two, three. Go!

432
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:12,320
Second one, get ready.

433
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,120
One, two, three. Go!

434
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:15,200
Third one, ready?

435
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,080
Take a deep breath,
close your eyes. Here we go.

436
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:19,000
One, two, three. Go!

437
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Okay.

438
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,800
Okay, where are the other parachutes?

439
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,200
There's only one left.

440
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,880
The parachute for the last passenger.

441
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,480
Why wasn't this checked beforehand?

442
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,320
That was Chaba's job!

443
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,880
She was too busy being fake
and filming her content.

444
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:35,880
Where is Chaba anyway?

445
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:39,480
That's right.

446
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,320
I'm right here filming another content!

447
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:42,680
Open your eyes and look!

448
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,680
If we're going to survive,
we have to survive "glam," right?

449
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,880
I've prepared them for everyone.

450
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,160
Then, where are they?

451
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:51,120
They're in the big bag that
Penelope hauled onto the plane.

452
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,560
The one she was carrying on her back.

453
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:54,680
Don't tell me...that bag?

454
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,080
Yeah, that bag.

455
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,080
Three, two, one!

456
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,640
Kree!

457
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,360
There's no need to thank me,
everyone.

458
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:06,840
It is my duty to
take care of every passenger.

459
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:25,040
Welcome to my video VLOG Day 1.

460
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:28,720
Glamorous Airline's
first-ever plane crash!

461
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,120
Hey, Chaba!

462
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:33,200
How about we survive first
before sharing the experience?

463
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,760
Can't I just record for now?
Someone will come to rescue us anyway.

464
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:39,400
We have no idea where we are.
I don't even know if there are any people here.

465
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:42,600
All-New...All-New,
you graduated in Agriculture, right?

466
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,600
Do you know where we are right now?

467
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,000
All-New?

468
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:47,840
Where did All-New go?

469
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:48,600
All-New!

470
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,840
All-New!

471
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:52,440
I know where we are.

472
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,440
Where is this place?

473
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:56,240
My home.

474
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Home sweet home.

475
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,280
I actually get All-New.

476
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:07,520
He must have truly lost all hope.

477
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:09,120
So he decided to go crazy first...

478
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:11,120
so he wouldn't have to face reality.

479
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,760
Are we really going to die here?

480
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:17,240
I don't want to die!

481
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,840
No, please!

482
00:20:18,840 --> 00:20:20,160
We're definitely going to die.

483
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:21,560
We're going to end up dead right here.

484
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:22,880
Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

485
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:24,640
Don't lose hope just yet.

486
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,480
Okay.

487
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,840
That was easy.

488
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,880
Guys, does anyone have anything with you?

489
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:30,680
I do!

490
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:33,680
I have my bags and expensive clothes.

491
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,040
How about the others?

492
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,920
All-New, what did you bring?

493
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:42,560
For what?

494
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:46,280
I was weighing Christopher at the time
so it just ended up in my hand.

495
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:49,560
Chai, we were born with nothing.

496
00:20:50,360 --> 00:20:52,840
Other things...they aren't that important.

497
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:55,280
All-New, just get lost already!

498
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:58,560
Is he okay?

499
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,560
Sky, what did you bring?

500
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,600
I'm the only one with the life grip.

501
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,480
I have drinking water.

502
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,760
Water!

503
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,720
Sky, can I have a sip?

504
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:11,120
Don't drink it all, Gift!

505
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,800
I'm so thirsty, let me have a sip.

506
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:13,520
Wait...

507
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:14,480
I finished it.

508
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,320
What?

509
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:18,960
So that means...
we're going to die of dehydration now?

510
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:23,080
Hey, stop triggering Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

511
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,720
Let's split up and search...

512
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:27,520
to see if there's water, people,
or anything that can help us.

513
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,600
He's right.

514
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:32,280
We should all help each other.

515
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,720
Alright, fine. Let's split up.

516
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:35,880
I'll go this way.

517
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,880
Go, go, go!

518
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,600
Wait, Chaba.

519
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:43,320
Huh?

520
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:45,760
What are you supposed to be doing?

521
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:47,360
Scouting the location!

522
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:48,400
For tonight's shelter.

523
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,360
It's dangerous, you know.

524
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:51,040
There are tigers.
I can hear them.

525
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:52,040
Where? What?

526
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,360
There's a sound!

527
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:54,760
Unbelievable.
So you're just going to take advantage of us?

528
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,840
I'm not taking advantage of anyone.

529
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:59,240
Bring back plenty of water and some coconuts.
I'm thristy.

530
00:21:59,240 --> 00:21:59,640
Yes, ma'am.

531
00:21:59,640 --> 00:21:59,760
Yeah.

532
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:00,760
Thank you.

533
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:05,760
Everyone,
I've found some mushrooms.

534
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:06,920
Even though the shape
is a bit strange...

535
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,920
these should be enough to keep us alive.

536
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:15,680
Thank you.

537
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:18,040
I'm honored that you allowed me
to scout with the two of you.

538
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,840
The two of us?
How did you count?

539
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:25,720
Well, I meant Ms. Petchgam Ploy,
plus you and me...

540
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,720
You're the one who asked to come along!

541
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:30,600
How could I let a delicate woman
walk out here all alone?

542
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:34,080
All alone?
I'm a woman too, you know!

543
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,760
The two men.

544
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:37,560
Are you messing with me?

545
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:40,480
No, look over there!
Those two men!

546
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,640
Hey, you're right!

547
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,640
There are two men getting off a boat.

548
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:48,040
In that case, should we go
get everyone and bring them here?

549
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:48,560
Good idea.

550
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,320
Let's go.

551
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:51,320
Hurry, let's go!

552
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:56,160
Hey, are those people?
Are they lost?

553
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,880
Are you stranded, right?

554
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,840
You're lucky you ran into us.

555
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,720
Boats hardly ever stop at this island.

556
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,200
Hey!

557
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,560
Get out of here right now!

558
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,920
And don't you come back
to this island for a long while.

559
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,160
Do you understand what I'm saying?

560
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:10,040
And don't you dare tell anyone about this!

561
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:12,040
Yes, yes! We're leaving!

562
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:16,800
Where's the boat?

563
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:17,960
Wait...

564
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,240
Wait...

565
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:22,680
A boat?
I don't see a single boat.

566
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:24,200
Is there one?

567
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,760
But we all saw the boat together
just a second ago, didn't we?

568
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:27,920
No.

569
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,160
I think we're all starting to hallucinate.

570
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:30,800
What?

571
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,120
I think we really are starting to see things.

572
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,120
Look, I can see a walking reef over there.

573
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,960
It's me, not a reef!

574
00:23:53,520 --> 00:23:56,040
This place is deserted.
Like, totally abandoned.

575
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:59,400
It's even more deserted
than in the movies, guys.

576
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,680
I'm afraid it won't be like in the movies.

577
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,080
If it were like the movies,

578
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,200
someone would have come to rescue us
by now, right?

579
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:08,880
No way. I can't die here.

580
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,400
I have so much money left,
I haven't even spent any of it!

581
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,640
Serves you right.

582
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:14,760
No matter how much money you have,
you're dying here with the rest of us.

583
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:17,200
That's not it.
I bet someone is hiding something.

584
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:21,200
Kree, do you have anything?
Kratom water? Anything? Out with it!

585
00:24:21,560 --> 00:24:23,520
Look, all I have is this match.

586
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,480
And it's the only one I've got.

587
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:25,080
That's not water.

588
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,080
It's not water, see?

589
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:28,520
Kree!

590
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,880
Did you seriously just
throw away the only match you had?

591
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:32,880
The only one?

592
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,840
Hey, Chai!

593
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:36,840
Calm down.

594
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,160
Calm down.

595
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:42,800
Kree did the right thing.

596
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:44,560
If we use that match...

597
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,800
it could start a forest fire.

598
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:50,640
Destroying nature, it's not good.

599
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:52,600
Destroying nature? No, no, no.

600
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,280
I can't take this anymore!

601
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:56,600
Chaba!

602
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,320
Do you have a human brain
or a donkey brain?

603
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,040
The plane crashed
and you brought clothes and money?

604
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,360
That is so incredibly stupid.

605
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:05,720
Honestly, you shouldn't be named Chaba,
you should be named Cha-donkey.

606
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:08,200
Sky, you're the selfish one!

607
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,160
You brought water but drank it all yourself.

608
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:12,320
Didn't you even think about
sharing a single drop with your friends?

609
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:17,040
Tid-Gift, the bottle is this small!
And you're trying to snatch it from me?

610
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:19,040
And... Cut!

611
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:21,240
Cut? Cut what?

612
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:24,240
The test ends here.
Everyone can go home now.

613
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,760
A test? What test?

614
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:30,000
Yes, a test.

615
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,600
This plane was scheduled
to be decommissioned and land right here.

616
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,000
It didn't actually crash.
But what did "crash"...

617
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,440
was all of you.

618
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:41,000
All of you failed the survival...

619
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,600
and rescue procedures.

620
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,600
Plus, you ended up fighting like this.

621
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:47,320
I'm so sorry.

622
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:50,320
None of you are "First Class."
You're dismissed.

623
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:54,480
So, we aren't stranded?

624
00:25:54,480 --> 00:25:56,120
Aha.

625
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,000
But we're unemployed?

626
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:58,320
Yes.

627
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:01,360
So...am I supposed to
be happy or sad about this?

628
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,920
You can figure that out later, Ms. Sky.

629
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:05,520
But right now, I feel all sticky.

630
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,280
I'm dying for a shower.

631
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,440
Let's head that way, shall we?

632
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:10,320
There's a souvenir shop along the way...

633
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:11,960
in case you want to stop
and buy some things.

634
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:12,960
So, please...

635
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:14,240
Let's go.

636
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,760
It's time to go home.

637
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:18,960
Come on, buddy.

638
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:19,960
Let's go home.

639
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:21,560
No.

640
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:22,920
This is my home.

641
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:24,280
Huh?

642
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,840
Finally, I've found my home.

643
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:37,760
The sun, the air...this is it.

644
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:41,960
Wait, I thought you weren't going?
Now you're leading the way!

645
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:45,960
Chai, I haven't even moved
from this spot yet.

646
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:51,520
Oh. We must have taken a wrong turn.

647
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:52,640
It should be that opening over there.

648
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,640
Come on, follow me.

649
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:59,480
I have a bad feeling about this.

650
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,480
Maybe it's this opening?

651
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,920
That was the first one we tried.

652
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,360
Ah! Or maybe that one?

653
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:05,360
That's a cliff.

654
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:08,480
That one, then!

655
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:10,920
No, we came from the sea over that way.

656
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,720
Or maybe way over there?

657
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,120
That's a rainforest.

658
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:17,120
It's terrifying in there,
I just got back.

659
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,800
Or...

660
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:21,880
Maybe...

661
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,400
Could it be...

662
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,880
Perhaps...

663
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:26,880
we're really stranded?

664
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,400
Captain!

665
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:38,760
Captain! Wait, wait...

666
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,760
Can we do that again? The door...

667
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:43,520
Something’s not right.

668
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:45,400
So...

669
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,000
that means...

670
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,080
what...

671
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,080
is...

672
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,760
Hey!

673
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:53,760
What?

674
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:54,640
You actually scared me!

675
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,560
What?

676
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:58,680
That was real?
It's called acting.

677
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,200
Then why didn't you say your line?

678
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,520
Hey wasn't in the script!

679
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,160
Yes, it was! You were supposed to say "Hey!"

680
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:04,760
I already said it, so why did you say it again?

681
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,760
You didn't say it, so I said it!

682
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:14,280
Let's go again.

683
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:16,280
Alright, as soon as we hit 5-4-3-2,
you stand up.

684
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:19,840
Perfect.

685
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,520
It needs to be more than perfect. Fabulous!

686
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:23,800
Fabulous!

687
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:24,600
Yeah.

688
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,520
Lin, you don't have to be scared at all.

689
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,520
Don't be scared, Lin.
Say fabulous and then clap.

690
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:28,880
Clap like this, really loudly.

691
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:33,120
Fabulous! Fabulous! Fabulous!
Fabulous! Fabulous!

692
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:34,400
Okay.

693
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,000
Very good!

694
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,280
Ms. Penelope, can you actually fly a plane?

695
00:28:40,280 --> 00:28:42,640
I can...

696
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,560
...not.

697
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:44,760
How can I fly a plane, you idiot?

698
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:45,480
You, idiot!

699
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,480
How can I fly a plane, you idiot?

700
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:48,520
How can I fly a plane, you idiot?

701
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:49,840
You idiot!

702
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:51,600
How can I fly a plane, you idiot?

703
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:52,440
You, idiot!

704
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,280
How can I fly a plane, you idiot?

705
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:55,280
You, idiot!

706
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:59,680
He's a veggie fetish...a veggie freak.

707
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:02,720
Plants aren't like humans.

708
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:06,000
Humans...humans are fickle.

709
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:10,000
Once you try to love them, then humans...

710
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:13,360
They aren't like humans.

711
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,520
Humans are fickle.

712
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:17,520
Once you try to love them, then it...

713
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,480
I'm confused too when I read it!

714
00:29:20,480 --> 00:29:23,480
I was rooting for you!
I was really rooting for you!

715
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,200
Maybe we really are stranded...

716
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:35,640
Can we get that a bit more high-pitched?

717
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:46,360
We haven't had anything for two days now,
All-New.

718
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,200
I'm starting to get hungry.

719
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,720
I don't know what kind of mushroom this is,
but it looks damn delicious.

720
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,560
A bear!

721
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,400
It’s like the nature on this island...

722
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,400
is absolutely furious with us.

723
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,160
Oh, this is really happening.

724
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:03,240
I think the best solution for everyone...

725
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:05,680
is that we need to get off this island
as fast as possible.

726
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:07,160
Kree!

727
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,720
Calm down, Mushroom-Eared Bear, okay?

728
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,720
Wait, this is Tik Jes!
